
“Peleg! Peleg!” said Bildad, lifting his eyes and hands, “thou thyself, 
as I myself, hast seen many a perilous time; thou knowest, Peleg, what it is to 
have the fear of death; how, then, can’st thou prate in this ungodly guise. 
